- Across models, test performance ranged from R2 = 0.72 to 0.99, yet training emissions varied by four orders of magnitude, from 0.001 g CO2 (simple linear regression) to 2.3 g CO2 (XGBoost).
- Although XGBoost achieved the highest accuracy (R2 = 0.9947), it emitted approximately 2300× more CO2 than regularised polynomial linear models for only a 0.39-point gain in R2. Pareto analysis identifies Lasso and Ridge regression with degree-4 polynomial features as sustainability-optimal, reaching R2 = 0.9908 at ~0.004 g CO2.
